{"id": "duc04-testb-22:2#7", "contents": "Krstic's arrest is significant not only because of his high rank but also due to his close association with other prominent war crimes suspects, including Gen. Ratko Mladic and Radovan Karadzic. As a colonel in 1995, Krstic was the deputy commander of the Drina battalion and was promoted to general shortly after the fall of Srebrenica. He is considered capable of implicating Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic, who has not been indicted, if he is willing to testify. Louise Arbour, chief prosecutor of the International Criminal Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia, welcomed the arrest, calling Krstic \"a very significant military leader.\""}
